List.EnumBOName: OR gate - output event occurs if any of the input events occurs
AND gate - output event occurs only when all the input events occurs simultaneously
K-out-of-N gate - output event occurs if any K or more of the input events occur

ProbCalcModesList.EnumBOName: The reliability data represents the probability  that the component is not able to perform  its function upon request.
Calculation by equation P=λ*t, where  λ – failure rate (1/hour);  t – failure exposure time (hours)
Calculation by equation P=λ*tm, where  λ – failure rate (1/hour);  tm – failure exposure time (hours)
Calculation by equation P(t) = 1-(1-q)*exp(-λ*t), where λ – failure rate (1/hour); t – failure exposure time (hours)
Calculation by equation P(t)=(λ/(λ+µ))*[1–exp(-(λ+µ)t)], P=λ/(λ+µ), where λ – failure rate (1/hour); µ - repair rate (1/MTTR) per hour
Calculation by equation P=λ*T, where λ – failure rate (1/hour); T – Inspection interval (hours)
Calculation by equation P=λ*T/2, where λ – failure rate (1/hour); T – Inspection interval (hours)
Calculation by equation  P(t) = 1-e^(-λ*T)/2, where λ – failure rate (1/hour); T – Inspection interval (hours)
